{"answer": "1. Calculate the total cost of the gas before cashback  
   \[
   \text{Total cost} = 10 \text{ gallons} \times \$3.00 \text{ per gallon}
   \]
   \[
   \text{Total cost} = <<10 \times 3.00>> = <<30.00>> \text{ dollars}
   \]

2. Calculate the total cashback earned  
   \[
   \text{Cashback} = 10 \text{ gallons} \times \$0.20 \text{ per gallon}
   \]
   \[
   \text{Cashback} = <<10 \times 0.20>> = <<2.00>> \text{ dollars}
   \]

3. Subtract the cashback from the total cost to find the final amount paid  
   \[
   \text{Final amount} = \text{Total cost} - \text{Cashback}
   \]
   \[
   \text{Final amount} = <<30.00 - 2.00>> = <<28.00>> \text{ dollars}
   \]

#### The gas will cost \$28.00 after the cashback rewards."}
